### Buyitem(UserID, GuildID, ItemID) => 
UserID - Id of the user who wants to buy the item    
GuildID - Guild ID for the guild    
ItemID - ID for the item    


> Returns: {             
  userID: UserID,   
  gid: GuildID,   
  wallet: User's Wallet Amt,   
  bank: User's Bank,  
  inventory: [ { Name: '1st ietm', Price: 1000, Sell: 50, id: 0 }, { Name: '2nd ietm', Price: 2000, Sell: 100, id: 1 } ],   
  lastUsedWeekly: Date And Time For Last Used Weekly Cmd
}

> Returns "NOT_ENOUGH_CASH" If the first user does not have enough cash

```
//Import package
const economy = require("@shinchanop/mongo-eco");
//create new economy() Class
const eco = new economy('YOUR MONGODB URI');


eco.Buyitem(UserID, GuildID, ItemID).then(data => {
      //<Channel>.send(`Succesfully bought item`)
})
```

